The paper deals with outlier detection using machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses challenges related to data management and processing, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.DM (Data Mining). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
